Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Friday and welcome back to our 38th Weekly Dose of Optimism.
Not too much to report on our end heading into the weekend. Lots of good st=
uff happening out there in this ole world of ours. We=E2=80=99re here to br=
ing it to you.
Let=E2=80=99s get to it.
The Weekly Dose is brought to you by... Tegus [ https://substack.com/redire=
ct/811badf4-65d7-43f2-85f5-2ec2925bc58b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_Z=
lNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Overcome market headwinds with fast, accurate, and cost-effective expertise=
=2E
Tegus [ https://substack.com/redirect/811badf4-65d7-43f2-85f5-2ec2925bc58b?=
j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] is the=
 affordable centralized research platform for at-cost expert calls, the lar=
gest and fastest growing expert transcript library of public and private ma=
rket data, and most robust benchmarking, charting and comps tooling.
With Tegus [ https://substack.com/redirect/811badf4-65d7-43f2-85f5-2ec2925b=
c58b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] y=
ou can spend less time collecting and connecting disparate data and start m=
aximizing what sets you apart =E2=80=93 your unique synthesis and decision =
making.=C2=A0
Ready to unlock the power of Tegus? Trial the benefits for free now below:
(1) E.P.A. Lays Out Rules to Turbocharge Sales of Electric Cars and Trucks =
[ https://substack.com/redirect/ae8ada79-e54f-42c9-9cbc-6c3118995850?j=3Dey=
J1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Coral Davenport [ https://substack.com/redirect/c38d16d4-9754-4973-807d-643=
c827058fb?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U ] for The New York Times
The Biden administration is proposing rules to ensure that two-thirds of ne=
w cars and a quarter of new heavy trucks sold in the United States by 2032 =
are all-electric.
It seems as if EVs are not only here to stay, but that they=E2=80=99ll near=
ly 10x over the coming decade. Politics and views on government overreach a=
side, this is an ambitious plan that puts the U.S. on track to achieve its =
emissions slashing goals.
Are EVs our planet=E2=80=99s saving grace? I don=E2=80=99t think so. They m=
ay be part of the story, but not the whole thing. I think some combination =
of technologies that make solar, nuclear, and fusion abundant will do more =
to solve our climate issues than restricting combustion engine cars.=20
Whatever your views on Elon, he was about two decades ahead of his time on =
this whole EV trend. And if you subscribe to Tim Urban=E2=80=99s theory of =
Elon [ https://substack.com/redirect/370d78c8-ddad-4e2c-bb4d-3b280081fc41?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], this p=
roliferation of EVs from other automakers was always part of the plan, too.=
 High end EVs =E2=80=94> mass-market EVs =E2=80=94> automaker competition =
=E2=80=94> more sustainable energy future=E2=80=A6a long and winding path f=
or sure, but it=E2=80=99s seems like things are tracking to plan.
(2) One of the biggest battery recycling plants in the US is up and running=
 [ https://substack.com/redirect/e0041677-32fc-45c2-8edf-b69a5fe6c230?j=3De=
yJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Julian Spector [ https://substack.com/redirect/d0a12a33-b1de-4298-b59f-f4c8=
76995a74?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU=
 ] for Canary Media
This is an early example of a=C2=A0nationwide movement to cost-effectively =
recycle and repurpose EV batteries as more and more drivers go electric. In=
 previous decades, companies hadn=E2=80=99t invested much in lithium-ion re=
cycling, but investment soared [ https://substack.com/redirect/3f7438a0-27d=
f-493f-a7b6-64ded1abfb88?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKb=
qOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] in the last few years to match the spiking demand for ba=
ttery materials [ https://substack.com/redirect/a0a82ea3-99dc-4c28-9f2d-9e8=
c6538cfd2?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U ].
As EVs proliferate, so too will demand for the critical minerals and compon=
ents that make EVs possible, like lithium-ion batteries. While the price of=
 lithium has plummeted in the last few months, our view is that there will =
be steadily increasing demand for these materials over the coming decades a=
s the clean energy revolution trucks along. And with 50 million+ (Not Borin=
g estimation) EVs being produced each year by 2032, we=E2=80=99re going to =
need a way to recycle and repurpose those cars=E2=80=99 components.
In the U.S. those EV component recycling facilities are already coming onli=
ne. The new factory mentioned in the story will be able to recycle over 70,=
000 EV battery packs annually (almost 9% of US EV sales in 2022.)
As with any new major technology, there will be shakeups, but new industrie=
s and job (such as EV battery recycling) will be created to fill the void.
(3) Mortality in the past: every second child died [ https://substack.com/r=
edirect/99d5154d-ce2f-4921-aaa5-bce5f71079b3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7=
GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Max Roser [ https://substack.com/redirect/3ba47b03-e057-47b0-a412-ba6161b92=
d8b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] fo=
r Our World in Data
The chances that a newborn survives childhood have increased from 50% to 96=
% globally.
There is perhaps not a more convincing statistic that life, broadly speakin=
g, has improved than: =E2=80=9CIn our lifetime, the global death rate of ch=
ildren declined from around 50% to 4%.=E2=80=9D=20
Comparatively, no other stat really even matters. Literacy rates? Doesn=E2=
=80=99t matter if you can read if you=E2=80=99re likely to die before high =
school. Living older? Adding an incremental 2-3 years towards the end of li=
fe does basically nothing to age averages when 50% of the population dies b=
efore 15 (leaving 40+ years on the table). Democracy? That=E2=80=99s double=
d in the last 50 years, but what good is freedom when you die before you ca=
n even vote.
You get the idea. Life has gotten much better because much more life has be=
en lived (on average) over the past 50 years. And much more life has been l=
ived largely because less children are dying.
(4) 2023 State of Crypto Report: Introducing the State of Crypto Index [ ht=
tps://substack.com/redirect/7a7000ce-6e69-479a-8f4b-4681fabdede2?j=3DeyJ1Ij=
oiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Daren Matsuoka, Eddy Lazzarin, Robert Hackett, Stephanie Zinn for a16zCrypt=
o [ https://substack.com/redirect/e160ba2d-edf3-4bf0-97c1-62b019ed440f?j=3D=
eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Packy here. On Tuesday, a16z crypto released its annual State of Crypto Rep=
ort, and its chock full of optimistic data on web3. I particularly like thi=
s framework, which the team developed a few years ago, showing that token p=
rices drive the things that actually matter: consumer interest, developer a=
ctivity, and new companies. Those things grew in 2022 despite the fall in p=
rices.=20
It=E2=80=99s also timely. On Monday, I wrote Crypto (Could) Fixes This [ ht=
tps://substack.com/redirect/9d78b74e-08d6-43d4-a34f-1aa781d63a10?j=3DeyJ1Ij=
oiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], and one of the =
main critiques I received is that you don=E2=80=99t actually need crypto. M=
astodon exists, and it doesn=E2=80=99t touch crypto. Here=E2=80=99s my resp=
onse:
Mastodon is a pretty brutal experience, and most of the people who onboarde=
d when Twitter looked to be falling apart had stopped using it just a coupl=
e months later [ https://substack.com/redirect/8c82feff-a49e-400d-b6cb-bf6b=
e6eed0d1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU=
 ]. But because crypto incentivizes developers to build all sorts of compos=
able software that makes crypto more usable generally, the experience of on=
boarding to a decentralized social platform like Farcaster and the apps bui=
lt on top is already much easier than Mastodon, and constantly getting bett=
er. Bubbles have value if they leave behind useful infrastructure, and a16z=
=E2=80=99s framework captures that well.=20
Not all of the data in the report is great for crypto/web3. a16z=E2=80=99s =
new State of Crypto Index [ https://substack.com/redirect/c2d0bedb-8b6f-4ab=
4-bc1e-42179954b1cb?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8=
-6m8ExkRNpU ], which looks at innovation and adoption indicators instead of=
 price, is down 5.86% YoY (much less than prices).=20
But the biggest lesson I took from the report is captured by the graphic I =
put at the top of this section =E2=80=94 great startups are built in every =
kind of market. I=E2=80=99m excited to see the logos that get added to that=
 graphic over the next few years.=20
(5) Generative Agents: Interactive Simulacra of Human Behavior [ https://su=
bstack.com/redirect/e252f55f-cf6a-47cc-a2f8-4b7fd770c5b4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3=
QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Joon Sung Park [ https://substack.com/redirect/3a66e152-a54d-49a0-802f-f2b3=
f7b1d624?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU=
 ], Joseph C. O'Brien [ https://substack.com/redirect/8e8077b0-d9b3-4bf1-9d=
