XXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], Percy Liang [ https://substack.com/redirect/d24d8=
88d-72c1-4567-b202-b2ed78e02cfb?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjm=
lXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], Michael S. Bernstein [ https://substack.com/redi=
rect/37f2be3c-28c5-4d72-a303-f7af4123e974?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA=
_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
As this tweet [ https://substack.com/redirect/1d6036a5-8ac7-4676-b1c9-f3e6b=
2abc174?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU =
] (thanks Elon) pointed out, a team of researchers created what is basicall=
y an AI-powered The Sims. The study uses =E2=80=9Cgenerative agents", power=
ed by ChatGPT, to simulate believable individual and social human behaviors=
=E2=80=A6and it worked. The =E2=80=9Cagents=E2=80=9D were making friends, d=
ating, and even pulling off things we humans can=E2=80=99t, like coordinati=
ng arrival times to parties.
Something something the next big thing will start out looking like a toy so=
mething something. First, this seems like it=E2=80=99d be pretty important =
in any kind of rollout of the Metaverse. Interact with NPCs in a realistic,=
 human-like way. Maybe Westworld isn=E2=80=99t that far off. Secondly, and =
perhaps more realistically, a tool like this could help simulate scenarios =
and inform decision making =E2=80=94 how will x population react to y, what=
 characteristics of q would z find most attractive? Play those scenarios ou=
t a million times in seconds, using agents that behave like humans, and my =
bet is that result will be pretty similar to how real humans would behave.
Bonus: The Problem of Abundance [ https://substack.com/redirect/3bf5a697-dd=
e3-415a-ae69-5a87c4254193?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepK=
bqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] (=F0=9F=94=92)
Martin Gurri [ https://substack.com/redirect/524c06f4-1e29-4b9c-ad92-ae5249=
732a10?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]=
 for The Free Press
We in the twenty-first century benefit from a revolutionary historical proc=
ess that has lavished on us unprecedented amounts of wealth and leisure. De=
irdre McCloskey has christened this the Great Enrichment. But we could just=
 as well call it the Great Emptiness, since it has drained from our lives t=
he old implacable conditions that once structured meaningful behavior.
This one is paywalled, but it=E2=80=99s worth the read if you subscribe to =
The Free Press or have a friend who does. Gurri, the author of The [ https:=
//substack.com/redirect/8e0efb9f-5e44-45b8-afc0-d76850b57769?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOX=
AwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]  [ https://substack.=
com/redirect/8e0efb9f-5e44-45b8-afc0-d76850b57769?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb=
8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]Revolt of the Public [ https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/8e0efb9f-5e44-45b8-afc0-d76850b57769?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ=
3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], discusses something we=
=E2=80=99ve been wrestling with in Not Boring: the messy fact that abundanc=
e doesn=E2=80=99t equal happiness, and in some cases, might actually detrac=
t from it.=20
We put this in the Bonus section, because it=E2=80=99s not optimistic. It=
=E2=80=99s counter to a lot of what we want to believe. But it=E2=80=99s a =
good reminder that as we celebrate the incredible things humans are able to=
 build and achieve, we need to put as much effort towards figuring out how =
to replace the meaning people derive from struggling to survive.=20
Double Bonus: Our portfolio company, Oasis, launched Oasis AI in the App St=
ore this week. Essentially, you talk into the app, and it transcribes your =
words and turns them into emails, essays, tweets, and more. It=E2=80=99s ma=
gical, and I use it daily to capture the random thoughts I have when I=E2=
